what is data skew?
    Data skew is when your data is unevenly distributed across partitions — meaning some partitions have a lot of data, while others have very little or none.
    🔹 Simple way to understand
    Imagine 3 partitions:
    Partition 0 → 1 GB data 😓
    Partition 1 → 10 MB 🙂
    Partition 2 → 5 MB 🙂
    👉 One partition is overloaded → this is data skew

what is Data shuffle?
    Data shuffle in Spark is when data is moved across partitions (and often across machines) so that the right data ends up together for processing.